 mill drew Cyprian Hart to New Britain","body":"Hart's New Britain grist mill was later operated by the Hooker descendant Cyprian Hart, who came to town to run it."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"short":"Andrews, Genealogical History of Deacon Stephen Hart (1875)","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/25/Geneological_history_of_Deacon_Stephen_Hart_and_his_descendants%2C_1632._1875%2C_%28IA_geneologicalhist01andr%29.pdf"},{"short":"FamilySearch"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"elijah-hart-1711"},"I00137":{"id":"I00137","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1682,"month":4,"day":12,"city":"Farmington","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1731,"month":3,"day":4,"city":"East Guilford","state":"Connecticut"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM038"},"parents":{"mother_research_notes":"Ruth Hawkins (daughter of Anthony Hawkins of Farmington)","father_id":"X00045","mother_id":"X01721"},"church_roles":[{"role":"Second Tutor, Yale College","dates":"1703-1705","notes":"Bespoken as tutor on the day of his graduation. Preceded by Daniel Hooker (first tutor, 1702), who was a son of Rev. Samuel Hooker of Farmington (H00007) and brother-in-law of Rev. James Pierpont, Yale's founding patron."},{"role":"Pastor","location":"East Guilford (now Madison), Connecticut","dates":"ordained Nov 25, 1707 – died Mar 4, 1731","notes":"Granted 25 acres by town of Guilford as settlement. \"One of the first Eminence of preachers in his Day\" (Rev. Thomas Ruggles Jr.). \"A gentleman of eminent piety\" (Rev. John Devotion). About 80 members added to church during his pastorate. In 1722, signed Rector Cutler's petition expressing doubt of Presbyterian ordination — later resolved his doubts and remained in place. President Stiles: \"Mr. Hart 